        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 7:55PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 755 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Marshall, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Marshall.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
